<s> Another twist is that we need to support implementations that understand indexes natively and efficiently, and those that have indexed interfaces grafted on to a tree or linked list internal data structure.  </s>
<s> When looping over all child nodes, or all nodes returned by getElementsByTag name, we DO NOT want to force the user to call the size()  </s>
<s> [or whatever we ended up calling it; sorry I'm in a hurry ...] method to figure out how far to loop, because that might force the implementation to travel all the relevant Nodes and count them.  </s>
<s> Instead, we let DOM  </s>
<s> programmers loop until an indexed lookup returns an error, which can be efficient with either implementation.  </s>
<s> So, we DO NOT consider index out of bounds conditions as a programming error, but something that we expect under normal circumstances.  </s>
